kubectl-argo-rollouts dashboard  
To load the dashboard

kubectl-argo-rollouts promote django-rollout
ğŸ’¡ This skips the remaining pause steps and fully deploys the new version.

kubectl-argo-rollouts restart django-rollout
ğŸ’¡ This forces a new rollout and restarts the pods.


kubectl-argo-rollouts set-step django-rollout --index=2
ğŸ’¡ Use this to move to a specific step in the canary deployment.


kubectl-argo-rollouts rollback django-rollout
ğŸ’¡ This reverts the rollout to the previous version.


kubectl-argo-rollouts get rollout django-rollout
ğŸ’¡ Shows pod count, progress, and current step.


kubectl-argo-rollouts history django-rollout
ğŸ’¡ Useful for tracking version changes.


kubectl-argo-rollouts get rollout django-rollout --watch
ğŸ’¡ Shows live updates on the rollout process.


kubectl-argo-rollouts abort django-rollout
ğŸ’¡ Cancels the rollout and keeps the current running version.



